<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB0FFEAFCCCFD9B4D1AFC15" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB0FFEAFCCCFD9B4AACFD55" blockId="1.[801,1452,588,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB0FFEAFCCCFD9B4AF9FD95" box="[839,923,589,612]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Notes. –</emphasis>
In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB0FFEAFBFDFD9A4C3BFD95" author="BURMAN" box="[1142,1369,588,612]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="228" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 228)</bibRefCitation>
cited a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB0FFEAFCAAFDBB4A02FD75" box="[801,864,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen and two illustrations (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB0FFEAFB48FDBB4CCAFD75" author="PETIVER J." box="[1219,1448,620,644]" journalOrPublisher="London" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" refId="ref10041" refString="PETIVER J. (1702 - 1709). Gazophylaciis naturae &amp; artis decades. London." title="Gazophylaciis naturae &amp; artis decades" type="book" year="1702">PETIVER, 1702 – 1709</bibRefCitation>
: tab. 61, fig. 2, 4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB0FFEAFCCCFD7A4D95FCD5" blockId="1.[801,1452,588,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB0FFEAFCCCFD7A4D33FD35" author="HOVENKAMP" box="[839,1105,684,708]" firstAuthor="HOVENKAMP" journalOrPublisher="Leiden Bot" page="209" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" refId="ref9529" refString="HOVENKAMP, P. H. (1986). A monograph of the fern genus Pyrrosia. Leiden Bot. Ser. 9." title="A monograph of the fern genus Pyrrosia" type="book" year="1986">HOVENKAMP (1986: 209)</bibRefCitation>
was the first to mention a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB0FFEAFAE6FD7B4CC9FD35" box="[1389,1451,685,708]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen at 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB0FFEAFC20FD1A4AA3FD15" box="[939,961,716,740]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="Herbarium">Gas</collectionCode>
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB0FFEAFC6EFD1A4D25FD15" box="[997,1095,716,740]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">holotype</typeStatus>
. This should be considered as an implicit lectotypification, as a single 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB0FFEAFB13FD3B4DB7FCF5" box="[1176,1237,749,772]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen representing original material is present in G-PREL.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB0FFEAFCCCFCFA4D1AFC15" blockId="1.[801,1452,588,996]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
An uncited specimen [
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB0FFEAFBBEFCFA4D2BFCB5" box="[1077,1097,812,836]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
00801093] from unknown origin is also extant in G-PREL: it bears a reference to one of Petiver’s illustrations (tab. 61, fig. 4. Tab. 61, fig. 2 is mentioned on the 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB0FFEAFC3FFC5B4A93FC55" box="[948,1009,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen), as well as the name of the new species, both in 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB0FFEAFC47FC7B4A81FC35" box="[972,995,941,964]" country="China" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13092" name="Nanjing University" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="Herbarium">N</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB0FFEAFC6CFC7B4A99FC35" box="[999,1019,941,964]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15678" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland, Leiden University branch" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" type="Herbarium">L</collectionCode>
. Burman’s handwriting, and thus should be regarded as original material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
